# Business Loan Malaysia for New Business: Fast Approval Guide for Startups & SMEs

Starting a new business in Malaysia? You'll need capital. Most entrepreneurs don't have RM50,000-200,000 sitting in the bank. That's where business loans for new businesses come in.

But here's the challenge: banks love existing businesses with proven track records. New businesses? Not so much. You haven't proven you can make money yet.

This guide shows you how to get approved for a business loan in Malaysia — even as a brand-new company.

## Why New Businesses Struggle to Get Bank Loans

Banks assess risk. New businesses represent higher risk because:

- **No financial history** — You can't show 2 years of audited accounts
- **No proven revenue** — Banks want to see consistent monthly income
- **Limited assets** — Nothing to pledge as collateral
- **Higher failure rates** — 60% of startups fail within 3 years

Traditional banks will often reject new business loan applications. But that doesn't mean you're stuck.

