## Frequently Asked Questions

**Can I get a business loan without SSM registration?**

No. All legitimate lenders require SSM registration. It proves your business legally exists. Register first (costs RM60-1,000 depending on structure).

**How long must my business operate before qualifying?**

- Banks: 2 years minimum
- Non-bank lenders: 3-6 months
- Government schemes: Varies (some accept brand new businesses)

**What if I have bad personal credit?**

Options narrow, but not impossible:
- Offer stronger collateral (property title)
- Get a guarantor with good credit
- Apply for smaller amounts (RM20k-50k)
- Government schemes may be more forgiving

**Can foreigners get business loans in Malaysia?**

Difficult. Most lenders require Malaysian IC. Exceptions:
- PR holders (permanent residents)
- Partnership with Malaysian majority shareholder
- Established business (3+ years) with strong revenue

**Should I use personal savings or take a loan?**

**Use savings for:** Initial setup, testing business idea, first 3 months
**Use loan for:** Scaling up, buying equipment, expanding

Don't drain all savings. Keep 3-6 months personal emergency fund.

